## Testing plan

- `build` gate: `dotnet build Berreman.slnx -c Release` from `Berreman/` MUST pass with all five `OpticalConstructor.*` projects + the Tests project + the existing Berreman/Analytics projects compiling in one pass, no new C# project (AC-A1).
- `unit-tests` gate: `dotnet test --no-build -c Release` from `Berreman/BerremanTests/` stays green (this slice does not touch `BerremanTests`).
- `constructor-unit-tests` gate: resolves to the descriptor at `.gates/OpticalConstructor/constructor-unit-tests.gates` (pass condition `exit_code: 0`) and runs `dotnet test … OpticalConstructor.Tests.fsproj -c Release`; the trivial passing test shipped in R-6's host makes it green from this slice's first round (reconciler round-4 §g — closed).
- Record the FuncUI-clone audit as NOT-YET-RUN and confirm no clone reference exists in `OpticalConstructor.Ui.fsproj` (AC-A8).

## Risks

- **Low/medium.** The risk is package-resolution drift (.NET 10 SDK, Avalonia / Avalonia.FuncUI / ScottPlot / WebView2 / Plotly.NET / OpenTK / Softellect.Sys / ALGLIB / System.Text.Json + FSharp.SystemTextJson / FSharp.Data / JsonSchema.Net / ClosedXML NuGet versions). Mitigation: add packages incrementally and keep placeholder modules empty so a failed reference is isolated. The public-vs-clone FuncUI distinction (above) is the load-bearing decision; getting it wrong reintroduces the spec-0110-class build failure.

## Hand-off

The five projects + the gated `OpticalConstructor.Tests` host build green at Release/x64 with placeholder modules. Later slices fill them: slice 002 (Domain foundation — units, beam tree, project aggregate), slice 003 (storage core — JSON/schema/sidecar), then the feature parts. The buildable FuncUI interpretation established here (public MIT NuGet, clone stays audit-gated) is relied on by every UI-touching slice. Emit the state-of-the-world file with all required ATX headings (`Where we are`, `What's working`, `Tests`, `Architecture`, `Deferred`, `Gotchas`, `Changelog`) and a fenced `gates:` YAML baseline block (e.g. `bm_unit_tests`, `constructor_unit_tests` counts) so the next slice's `count_at_least` gate has a baseline.
